{{Quote|<nowiki></nowiki>''Kholm''-grass has grown on Honoghr since the beginning of knowledge.|[[Vor'corkh]] to Leia Organa Solo|<ref name="The Last Command">''[[The Last Command]]''</ref>}}
'''''Kholm''-grass''{{'}} was a [[Plant/Legends|plant]] native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Honoghr/Legends|Honoghr]]. After the [[Battle of Honoghr/Legends|Battle of Honoghr]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the planet was devastated and much of its plant life died out.

[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] used this ecological catastrophe as a means to enslave the [[Noghri/Legends|Noghri]] people indefinitely. He sent them supplies to endear him to them, but replaced the ''kholm''-grass with a hybrid variant which continued to poison all other native plants. The [[Decon III|decon droids]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] provided were in fact sent there to prolong the economic devastation of the planet, removing the ''kholm''-grass as slowly as possible. The Noghri did notice the difference in the smell of the new ''kholm''-grass, but attributed it to the chemicals released by the ''[[Gahenna]]'' decades earlier.

During the [[Thrawn campaign]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] eventually [[Mission to Honoghr|discovered]] and revealed the truth of the new ''kholm''-grass to the Noghri, prompting them to [[Noghri revolution|leave]] the service of [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]].

